n\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum\">ChargeSpectrum</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓩</span></span>) =&gt; <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.mk\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">qHd</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.qHd\">qHd</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">qHu</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.qHu\">qHu</a></span>, <span class=\"fn\">Q5</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Insert.insert\">insert</a> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">q5</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.Q5\">Q5</a></span></span>, <span class=\"fn\">Q10</span> := <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.Q10\">Q10</a></span> <a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.mk\">}</a>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">T</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>       <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#EmptyCollection.emptyCollection\">∅</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span> ∉ <span class=\"fn\">T</span></span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Not\">¬</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a proposition `p` if `(T.uniqueMap4 (insert q10.1)).toMultiset.filter p`\nand `(T.uniqueMap3 (insert q5.1)).toMultiset.filter p` for all `q5 ∈ S5` and `q10 ∈ S10` then\nif `x ∈ T` and `x ⊆ y` if `y ∉ T` then `¬ p y`.\nThis assumes that all charges in `T` are complete, and that `p` satisfies\n`x ⊆ y → ¬ p x → ¬ p y`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/MinimalSuperSet.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.subset_insert_filter_card_zero","kind":"theorem","line":467,"name":"SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.subset_insert_filter_card_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L467-L487"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/MinimalSuperSet.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum.subset_insert_filter_card_zero_inductive\"><span class=\"name\">SuperSymmetry</span>.<span class=\"name\">SU5</span>.<span class=\"name\">ChargeSpectrum</span>.<span class=\"name\">subset_insert_filter_card_zero_inductive</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓩</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#DecidableEq\">DecidableEq</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓩</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Multiset/Defs.html#Multiset\">Multiset</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/Particles/SuperSymmetry/SU5/ChargeSpectrum/Basic.html#SuperSymmetry.SU5.ChargeSpectrum\">ChargeSpectrum</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝓩</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">S5 </span><span class=\"fn\">S10</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Defs.h